    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>diced carrot</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potato</strong> to the pot</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[780ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> vegetable stock</strong>,<strong> </strong>bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 15-18 min or until the carrot is fork-tender</p><p>While the soup is cooking, dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
